title: Deleting Repeated Lines in Two text files -python
body:
I have two .list files and i would like to print all the lines of the bigger file that are not in the smaller file. however, the strings will not == each other.

For ex:

ex1.list

-ABCD
-ABBD
-ACCD
-ADDD

ex2.list

-ABCD1
-ABBD2
-ACCD
-ADDD
-GHIJK

all the lines in ex1.list can be found somewhere in ex2.list. i would like to print the lines of ex2.list that cannot be found in ex1.list.

thank you!
